frameitem.name: Show Ink
frameitem.tt_text: Show InkŽShow or hide ink on the sheet.

frameitem.name: Protect Sheet
frameitem.tt_text:
Protect SheetŽPrevent unwanted changes from
others by limiting their ability to
edit.

For example, you can prevent
people from editing locked cells or
making formatting changes.

frameitem.name: Protect Workbook
frameitem.tt_text:
Protect WorkbookŽKeep others from making structural
changes to your workbook, such as
moving, deleting or adding sheets.

frameitem.name: Share Workbook
frameitem.tt_text:
Share WorkbookŽShare your workbook so that others
can work in it at the same time.

FYI: Workbooks containing tables
can't be shared.

frameitem.name: Protect and Share Workbook
frameitem.tt_text:
Protect and Share WorkbookŽShare the workbook and protect
change tracking with a password.

frameitem.name: Allow Users to Edit Ranges
frameitem.tt_text:
Allow Users to Edit RangesŽSet up password protection on
ranges, and choose people who can
edit those ranges.

Once set up, click Protect Sheet to activate the password-protected
ranges.

frameitem.name: Track Changes
frameitem.tt_text:
Track ChangesŽKeep track of changes made to this
document.

This is especially useful if the
document is almost done, and
you're working with others to make
revisions or give feedback.

frameitem.name: Workbook Views
frameitem.tt_text: Workbook Views

frameitem.name: Normal
frameitem.tt_text: NormalŽSee your document in Normal view.

frameitem.name: Page Break Preview
frameitem.tt_text: Page Break PreviewŽSee where the page breaks will appear when your document is printed.

frameitem.name: Page Layout
frameitem.tt_text:
Page LayoutŽSee how your printed document will look.

This is a good way to check out where pages begin and end, and to see any headers/footers on the page.

frameitem.name: Custom Views
frameitem.tt_text: Custom ViewsŽSave your current display and print settings as a custom view that you can quickly apply in the future.

frameitem.name: Ruler
frameitem.tt_text:
RulerŽShow rulers next to your document.

You can see and set tab stops, move table borders, and line up objects in the document. Also, you can measure stuff.

frameitem.name: Gridlines
frameitem.tt_text: View GridlinesŽShow the lines between rows and columns in the sheet to make the sheet easier to read.

frameitem.name: Formula Bar
frameitem.tt_text: Formula BarŽShow the formula bar so you can see formulas in cells.

frameitem.name: Headings
frameitem.tt_text: View HeadingsŽShow column headings and row numbers. Column headings are the letters or numbers that appear above the columns on a sheet.

frameitem.name: Zoom
frameitem.tt_text:
ZoomŽZoom to the level that's right for you.

For zoomier zooming, use the controls in the status bar.
100%ŽZoom your document to 100%.

frameitem.name: Zoom to Selection
frameitem.tt_text:
Zoom to SelectionŽZoom the sheet so the selected range of cells fills the entire window.

This can help you focus on a specific area of the sheet.

frameitem.name: New Window
frameitem.tt_text: New WindowŽOpen a second window for your document so you can work in different places at the same time.

frameitem.name: Arrange All
frameitem.tt_text: Arrange AllŽStack your open windows so you can see all of them at once.

frameitem.name: Freeze Panes
frameitem.tt_text:
Freeze PanesŽFreeze a portion of the sheet to keep it visible while you scroll through the rest of the sheet.

This is useful for checking out data in other parts of your worksheet without losing your headers or labels.

frameitem.name: Split
frameitem.tt_text: SplitŽDivide the window into different panes that each scroll separately.

frameitem.name: Hide
frameitem.tt_text:
HideŽHide the current window.

To bring the window back, click the Unhide button.

frameitem.name: Unhide
frameitem.tt_text: UnhideŽUnhide any windows hidden by the Hide Window feature.

frameitem.name: View Side by Side
frameitem.tt_text: View Side by SideŽInstead of switching back and forth between workbooks, view them side by side. It makes comparing them easier.

frameitem.name: Synchronous Scrolling
frameitem.tt_text:
Synchronous ScrollingŽScroll two documents at the same time.

This is a great way to compare documents line by line or scan for differences.

To use this feature, turn on View Side by Side.

frameitem.name: Reset Window Position
frameitem.tt_text:
Reset Window PositionŽPlace the documents you're comparing side by side so they share the screen equally.

To use this feature, turn on View Side by Side.

frameitem.name: Switch Windows
frameitem.tt_text: Switch WindowsŽQuickly switch to another open Excel window.

frameitem.tt_text: View Macros (Alt+F8)ŽSee a list of macros you can work with.¦1•View Macros (Alt+F8)ŽClick to view, record or pause a macro.

frameitem.name: Resize Table
frameitem.tt_text: Resize TableŽ Resize this table by adding or removing rows and columns.

frameitem.name: Summarize with PivotTable
frameitem.tt_text:
Summarize with PivotTableŽ Summarize the data in this table using a PivotTable.

PivotTables make it easy to arrange and summarize complicated data and drill down on details.

frameitem.name: Remove Duplicates
frameitem.tt_text:
Remove DuplicatesŽ Delete duplicate rows from a sheet.

You can pick which columns should be checked for duplicate information.

frameitem.name: Convert to Range
frameitem.tt_text:
Convert to RangeŽ Convert this table into a normal range of cells.

All of the data is preserved.

frameitem.name: Insert Slicer
frameitem.tt_text:
Insert SlicerŽ Use a slicer to filter data visually.

Slicers make it faster and easier to filter Tables, PivotTables, PivotCharts, and cube functions.

frameitem.tt_text: External Table Data

frameitem.tt_text: ExportŽ Export the data in this table to a SharePoint list or Visio diagram.

frameitem.name: Properties
frameitem.tt_text: Data Range PropertiesŽ Specify how cells connected to a data source will update, what contents from the source will be displayed, and how changes in the number of rows or columns in the data source will be handled in the workbook.

frameitem.name: Open in Browser
frameitem.tt_text: Open in BrowserŽ View the server version of this table in the web browser.

frameitem.name: Unlink
frameitem.tt_text:
UnlinkŽ Disconnect this table from the server.

It will no longer be kept up-to-date.

frameitem.name: Header Row
frameitem.tt_text:
Header RowŽ Turn on or off the header row of the table.

A header row formats the top row of the table specially.

frameitem.name: Total Row
frameitem.tt_text:
Total Row(Ctrl+Shift+T)Ž Turn on or off the total row of the table.

The total row is a row at the end of the table which displays totals for each column.

frameitem.name: Banded Rows
frameitem.tt_text:
